far\nabove 200 the next move in CBN.\nFOX FILM\u2014Many people believe\nFox will come through Its financial\ndifficulties in gcod shape. We think\nit a purchase near closing prices of\nIas^ week\nINTERNATIONAL HYDRO ELEC\nTRIC\u2014New high Saturday by several\npoints. Would hold stock for still\nhigher prices.\nBANK CLEARINGS.\nNEW YORK, Feb. 10.\u2014Bank clearings,\n$547,000,000; clearing house balances,\n$105,000,000; Federal Reserve Bank cred\nit balance, $102,000,000.\nCHICAGO, Feb.' 10.\u2014Bank clearings,\n$85,400,000; balances, $8,600,000.\nCOMMERCE HEAD\nSAYS BUSINESS\nOUTLOOK BETTER\nLamont Cites Increases\nin Employment at In-\ndustrial Cities.\nBy International News Service:\nWASHINGTON, Feb. 10.\u2014Secretary\nof Commerce Lamont said today there\nwas nothing disturbing in the coun\ntry\u2019s business outlook.\nEmployment conditions were im\nproving, the future of the construc\ntion industry was hopeful and steel\nmills were operating 80 percent, ac\ncording to a survey Just completed.\nIn making comparison to last year,\nLamont said it should be recalled\nJanuary and February of 1929 were\nexceptional months when records\nwere being created in many lines.\nReports from Detroit, headquarters\nof the automobile industry, indicated\nconditions there were improving, he\nsaid.\nAccording to his information, Rus\nsia is on a food ration basis and is\nnot expected to export wheat this\nyear, he asserted..\nBROAD STREET\nMART COMMENT\nBy HARRIS, UPHAM A Co.\nSteel should become a leader again j\nwhen general industrial list is ready j\nto move forward-investment buying\nhas been in progress\u2014in addition one j\nof the most important banking inter-\nests added a good sized block to out\nright holdings within the past week\nor ten days\u2014report of unfilled orders j\nas of Jan. 31 to be published at noon!\ntoday should show a moderate in- j\ncrease. i\nView is held in many speculative j\nquarters that General Motors has\ngood trading possibilities around cur-\nrent levels. There has been talk that j\ncompany will have a larger margin of j\nprofit in first quarter this year, than j\nin final three months of 1929. There\nhave been periods of impressive buy\ning in the stock in recent sessions.\nPrincipal subsidiaries of New York\nCentral now are being operated by\nthat road under lease with result that\nearnings flow directly into the Cen\ntral\u2019s treasury, because of this change\nopinion is growing that prospects are\nbrighter for an increase in current $8\na share dividend rate to $10 a share\nin not distant future.\nActivity and strength in rails\nshould bring buying into Allegheny\ncorporation. Many traders who have\nbeen out of standard rails because of\nhigh selling levels and other factors\nhave been inclined to pick up Alle\ngheny because its holdings enhance\nin value as carrier issues move up\nward.\nCHICAGO GRAIN TABI.K.\nBy THOMSON-McKINNON.\nWHEAT\u2014 Open High Low Close\nMav .121 122 120% 122\nJuly .122 123 121% 123\nMar.110% 117% 116% 117%\nCOllN\u2014\nMay .92% 93 01% 92%\nJuly .94% 91% 98% 94%\nMar.88% 89% 88% 89\nOATS\u2014\nMay 40% 40% 40% 46%\nJuly .45% 45% 45% 45%\nMar. ..44% 45 44% 4o\nEYE\u2014\nMay .84 85 83 84%\nJuly S4% 85% 84% 81 ts\nMar.. 84 84 S2% S3%\nTOLEDO CASH GRAIN.\nTOLEDO, O., Feb. 10. Cash grain\nclose:\nWheat\u2014No. 2 red, $1.23%@S1.24%.\nCorn\u2014No. 3. yellow, 90(b.91c.\nRye\u2014No. 2. 35c.\nOats\u2014No. 2 white, 49%@50%c.\nBarley\u2014No. 2, 08c.\nClover\u2014Domestic cash old, $10.85: cash\nnew, $11: February, $11; February\nchoice, $11.40; March, $11.10: March\nchoice, $11.50.. Imported cash old, $9.\nTimothy\u2014Cash old, $3; cash'new $3.23;\nMarch, $3.40.\nAlsike\u2014Cash $10.65; Februnry, $10.05;\nMarch. $10.80.\nButter\u201437(fi>41c.\nEggs\u201430fS39c.\nHay\u2014$1.25 cwt.\nlIlltAliO LASH\n(CHICAGO. Feb. 10.\u2014Cash grain close:!\nWheat\u2014Sample grade red. $1.07; No. 2\nhard, $1.16%\u00ae'$1.17*4 No. 3, $1.1514; No.\n3 northern, $1.14; No. 2 yellow, 